Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolytes, both commercial and research, are used at 800-900 degrees C as solid oxide H2O electrolyzer cells (SOECs).
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis

Sentencas: When the operation is extended to current densities j corresponding to a steam-conversion rate above 100%, or when the steam supply is interrupted under constant current conditions, cell voltages saturate at similar to 1.9 V at 810 degrees C. A cell survives 64 h polarization at j=-0.34 A cm(-2) without any steam supply.
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis

Sentencas: The mechanism limiting the cell voltage is attributed to electronic conduction in the YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis

Sentencas: No indications are found for electrolyte decomposition.
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis

Sentencas: Because the saturation voltage exceeds typical operation voltages by several hundred millivolts, electrolyte conduction in the normal SOEC mode remains predominantly ionic.
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis

Sentencas: The rise in the cell voltage to the value determined by electronic conduction occurs when steam transport in the hydrogen/steam electrode becomes limiting.
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis

Sentencas: As a consequence of H2O back-diffusion from the cell exhaust in the used unsealed test configuration, the rise occurs at nonzero current density under zero steam supply.
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopic data are compared with and without steam supply and are qualitatively interpreted with an equivalent circuit model.
Titulo: Electronic Conduction of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Cells Operated in High Temperature Water Electrolysis
